==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[graybeard]]

===Etymology===
From [[grey]] + [[beard]]; men of advanced age would be expected to have a grey beard.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# An [[old]] [[man]].
# Metaphorically, the members of a group who have been there the longest (regardless or actual age or gender.)


